Founder of the People's Dialogue and former Johannesburg mayor, Herman Mashaba, announced he will be launching a new political party in August. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Founder of the People's Dialogue and former Johannesburg mayor, Herman Mashaba, says he would never want to go into a coalition with the ANC because of the level of corruption within the party. Mashaba announced he will be launching a new political party in August. He wants to contest elections in three Gauteng metros - Johannesburg, Ekurhuleni and Tshwane. READ: Herman Mashaba reveals plans for new political party Mashaba says he is shocked that some ANC councillors can be corrupt enough to steal food parcels and loot the state during the COVID-19 pandemic. "In the event that we don't get outright majorities in municipalities where we don't govern thenÂ we must go into a coalition government. I am happy to go into a coalition government with anyone, with the exception of the ANC", he said. Mashaba resigned from the Democratic Alliance in October 2019.